Warnings about key props
If you look in the console, when you are rendering multiple adjacent elements with JSX youâ€™ll see that React is mad at you for not adding something called a â€œkeyâ€ prop when you map over an array and render components.

At a high level, keys help React identify which items have changed, are added, or are removed. They should always be unique and not change (also called stable)

You donâ€™t need to worry about this for now; Weâ€™ll talk more about whatâ€™s happening here shortly. Letâ€™s get comfortable with the fundamentals first!

